AmaRharhabe Queen Noloyiso Sandile has been laid to rest at the Mngqesha Great Place on the outskirts of King William's Town. She died of COVID-19 last Wednesday. KING WILLIAM'S TOWN - The AmaRharhabe queen Noloyiso Sandile has been laid to rest at the Mngqesha Great Place on the outskirts of King William's Town. She died at the Cecilia Makiwane Hospital in Mdantsane last Wednesday of COVID-19. READ: AmaRharhabe Queen Noloyiso Sandile to be laid to rest Her son Jonguxolo Sandile is now the new ruler of the AmaRharhabe nation. The family spokesperson Prince Xhanti Sigcawu says the paperwork about the new king will be submitted to the government.